        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 7:35PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 735 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Three Rivers, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Ray Point, and Oakville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 64 and 75.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 618 and 622.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
